<TEXT>Your browser is unsupported We recommend using the latest version of IE11, Edge, Chrome, Firefox or Safari. University of Illinois Chicago Search the site University of Illinois Chicago Office of the Dean of Students Main Menu Expand About menu Expand Assistance menu Expand Community Standards menu Expand Student Veterans menu Eyebrow menu Diversity Education U & I Care Student Affairs UIC menu UIC.edu Campus Map Search U&ICare: Adjusting to Campus Life Posted on October 18, 2021 Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link Whether you are just beginning at UIC or are back for your final semester, the transition from summer to fall can be a difficult adjustment. Starting the year can bring a mix of emotions. You might feel excitement, but also some feelings of loneliness or anxiety about what’s ahead. Take some time to look into the various success units that UIC has to offer such as Peer Success Coaching Office of First Year Initiatives . It’s important to start off with a good self-care routine, which includes healthy eating, exercise, and healthy stress management.  Find resources that can support your mental health during this transition at the UIC Wellness Center UIC Counseling Center , UIC InTouch Crisis & Support Hotline , and the Office of the Dean of Students University of Illinois Chicago DOS Offices Career Services Student Employment Counseling Center Wellness Center For Employees SA Human Resources SA Technology GoTime Log-in The Pulse Safety UIC Police Office of Access & Equity Contact-US Giving Social Media Accounts xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Facebook xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Twitter xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Instagram xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? YouTube Contact 1200 West Harrison St., 3030 SSB Chicago, IL 60607 Phone: (312) 996-4857 dos@uic.edu UIC.edu links UIC.edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Opening